If you need to perform runtime checks based on the class you will need to pass it in as an argument to the function, just setting the type argument won&#39;t do since that will be erased during compilation:

```ts
const resolve = &lt;T&gt;(map: any[], ctor: new (...a: any) =&gt; T): T | null =&gt; {
    for (const value of map) {
        if (value instanceof T) {
            return &lt;T&gt; value;
        }
    }
    return null;
}
class A{}
class B{}

const map = [new A(), new B()];
const a = resolve(map, A);
const b = resolve(map, B);
```
